"title": "7306: ark of the covenant",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7306",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A rectangular wooden box, overlaid with gold, measuring 3.75 x 2.25 x 2.25 feet (1.1 x 0.7 x 0.7 metres). It contains the Law tablets and symbolises God's presence with his people.</p>\n<h2>Descriptions of the ark</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:22\">EXO 25:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:2\">LEV 16:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:33\">NUM 10:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:6\">JOS 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:5\">JOS 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:9\">JOS 4:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:11\">1SA 4:11</a></p>\n<h3>The construction of the ark</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:10-Exod25:16\">EXO 25:10–25:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:1\">DEU 10:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:1-Exod31:7\">EXO 31:1–31:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:10-Exod35:12\">EXO 35:10–35:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:1-Exod37:5\">EXO 37:1–37:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:3\">DEU 10:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:33\">EXO 39:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:35\">EXO 39:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:1-Exod40:5\">EXO 40:1–40:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:20-Exod40:21\">EXO 40:20–40:21</a></p>\n<h3>The construction of the atonement cover</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:17-Exod25:21\">EXO 25:17–25:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:34\">EXO 26:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:6\">EXO 30:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:6-Exod37:9\">EXO 37:6–37:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:35\">EXO 39:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:20\">EXO 40:20</a></p>\n<h2>The care of the ark</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:30-Num3:32\">NUM 3:30–3:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:5\">NUM 4:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:8\">DEU 10:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:9\">DEU 31:9</a></p>\n<h2>Major events in the history of the ark</h2>\n<h3>The ark is taken to the promised land</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:3\">JOS 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:6\">JOS 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:15-Josh3:16\">JOS 3:15–3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:4-Josh6:16\">JOS 6:4–6:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:33\">JOS 8:33</a></p>\n<h3>The ark is the focus of the covenant renewal at Mount Ebal</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:26-Judg20:28\">JDG 20:26–20:28</a></p>\n<h3>The ark is captured by the Philistines</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:1-1Sam4:11\">1SA 4:1–4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:17-1Sam4:22\">1SA 4:17–4:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam5:1-1Sam5:12\">1SA 5:1–5:12</a></p>\n<h3>The ark is returned to Israel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:1-1Sam6:3\">1SA 6:1–6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:10-1Sam6:15\">1SA 6:10–6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:19\">1SA 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:1-1Sam7:2\">1SA 7:1–7:2</a></p>\n<h3>The ark is brought to Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:1-2Sam6:12\">2SA 6:1–6:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:3-1Chr13:14\">1CH 13:3–13:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:17\">2SA 6:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:1\">1CH 16:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:1\">1CH 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:37\">1CH 16:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:2-2Sam7:7\">2SA 7:2–7:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:1-1Chr17:6\">1CH 17:1–17:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:24-2Sam15:25\">2SA 15:24–15:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:29\">2SA 15:29</a> <em>David is fleeing from Absalom.</em></p>\n<h3>The ark is placed in the temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:1-1Kgs8:6\">1KI 8:1–8:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:2-2Chr5:7\">2CH 5:2–5:7</a></p>\n<h3>The ark in later Israelite history</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:3\">2CH 35:3</a> <em>The ark must have been moved from the temple.</em></p>\n<h2>The function of the ark</h2>\n<h3>To contain the tablets of the Law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:5\">DEU 10:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:16\">EXO 25:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:21\">EXO 25:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:20\">EXO 40:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:24-Deut31:26\">DEU 31:24–31:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:9\">1KI 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:4\">HEB 9:4</a> <em>The jar of manna and Aaron's rod were originally placed beside the ark (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:34\">Ex 16:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num17:10\">Nu 17:10</a>), and were probably put inside it at a later date.</em></p>\n<h3>As the place where God reveals his commands to Moses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:89\">NUM 7:89</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:22\">EXO 25:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:6\">EXO 30:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:36\">EXO 30:36</a></p>\n<h3>As a symbol of the presence of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:2\">LEV 16:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:33-Num10:36\">NUM 10:33–10:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:6\">JOS 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:27\">JDG 20:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:2\">2SA 7:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:1\">1CH 17:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:41\">2CH 6:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:8\">PSA 132:8</a></p>\n<h3>Used on the Day of Atonement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:13-Lev16:15\">LEV 16:13–16:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The ark's holiness and effect</h2>\n<h3>Irreverent treament of the ark brings judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:6-2Sam6:7\">2SA 6:6–6:7</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:9-1Chr13:10\">1CH 13:9–13:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:4\">JOS 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam5:1-1Sam5:4\">1SA 5:1–5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam5:8-1Sam5:12\">1SA 5:8–5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:19\">1SA 6:19</a></p>\n<h3>The presence of the ark brings blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:11\">2SA 6:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:14\">1CH 13:14</a></p>\n<h2>A restored Israel in which the ark has no place</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:16\">JER 3:16</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The ark in John's revelation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:19\">REV 11:19</a></strong> <em>The ark here symbolises the presence of God and is open and visible, not hidden in the Most Holy Place.</em></p>",
